## 6. The 25% Conservative Model

Most tokenisation platforms use aggressive leverage. Tokenise.Farm inverts this deliberately.

**Max tokenisation = 25% of farm's appraised value**

- Tested against **40 years of UK farmland price data** — no drawdown has ever threatened a 25% position
- Matches collateralisation ratios used by UK agricultural lenders (NFU Mutual, Lloyds Agricultural)
- No forced liquidations under normal market conditions
- Farmer retains 100% ownership and control
- Token scarcity enforced on-chain at mint time — not by policy, by code

This is not a conservative choice made out of caution. It is a deliberate product decision that makes the platform lender-acceptable and regulator-compatible from day one.

